The paper deals with the impact of autonomous vehicles on traffic networks, which involves multi-agent systems and game theory (cs.MA and cs.GT). It also involves the use of traffic delay models and optimization techniques (cs.NI and cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential benefits and drawbacks of introducing autonomous vehicles, which could fall under the category of machine learning and decision making (cs.LG).
